 in the pipeline for ads ceo sort of sponsored by × search april   updated  berry plastics becoming berry global group comments email print by jim johnson berry plastics corp packaging extrusion film  sheet injection molding thermoforming more  updated — berry plastics group inc is changing its name and adopting a new logo in a move that is both a nod to the company’s past and a look toward the future the evansville indbased company will become berry global group inc april  and is already using the new logo changes which include a new set of company values and mission statement have been in the works since last fall when tom salmon became chief operating officer in anticipation of succeeding jon rich as ceo in february “for those of us who have been with the company for a while it really represents who we are today it’s just a fresh clean look” salmon said in a telephone interview from geneva switzerland where the company unveiled the moves april  “you have to look at it comprehensively between the name change the mission and the core values” berry now has  domestic and  international locations is looking to follow customers to different parts of the world as they continue to expand but the company will not grow for growth’s sake the ceo said “the majority of our business resides in north america it’s incredibly important to us it’s always going to be an incredibly important region to us but we also have to make certain that we’ve got the ability to deliver value internationally as well and that is definitely aspirational for us we’re going to be very smart about that we’re going to do that in a methodical measured way but our end customers expect it” salmon said a  acquisition of nonwovens maker avintiv inc with operations in  countries helped broaden berry’s international geography “there is opportunity where customers want to take advantage of those core values that berry represents we feel that our business has to reflect the opportunities that exist in other regions of the world we’re going to be prudent in evaluating those opportunities and making certain that it makes sense for our end customers but also our shareholders” salmon said virtually all of berry’s products use plastics “in one way or another” salmon said and the ceo does not believe eliminating the word “plastics” from the company’s name will have any impact berry plastics group inc salmon “plastics remain incredibly important to us it’s a core competency of ours it’s always going to be but we didn’t want to limit our thinking we didn’t want to limit it to that substrate in and of itself and we just felt that what’s important is ‘berry’ people know who we are” he said “that’s what people always refer to us as in the marketplace ‘berry’ they never use ‘berry plastics’” salmon said “i think this captures the essence of who we’ve been and who we really are” aside from the name change the company also has adopted a mission statement “always advancing to protect what’s important” the new logo features a diamond shaped icon in the upper right hand corner consisting of four parts each of a different color those sections represent the company’s new values of partnerships excellence growth and safety these values salmon said are high standards “but they are standards we expect to achieve and deliver on those commitments and those promises to our customers every day” berry also is changing the name of a wholly owned subsidiary from berry plastics corp to berry global inc the company unveiled the changes in conjunction with index  in geneva which bills itself as the world’s largest nonwovens exhibition berry is now a  billion company with more than  locations a far cry from the singlelocation business in evansville with less than  million in annual sales in  when the company became berry plastics salmon said “we think this is a fresh look for our company” salmon said about the changes “we’re excited the company is poised and this is a great opportunity” newsletter signu